passage_text: Counters Floors and More! Granicrete is a high-end cement overlay system that bonds to your existing counter tops or cement flooring. Granicrete gives you the elegant look of granite, marble, concrete, stone, tile, wood and more at a fraction of the price. Granicrete is very durable and Eco-friendly.

Granicrete is a durable polymer modified concrete mix used as a thin overlay for new or existing surfaces that can be colored to look like granite, marble stone or concrete. The Granicrete colors can be used as-is or mixed to produce virtually any color you desire.

THE REVOLUTIONARY GRANICRETE COUNTER TOP RESURFACING SYSTEM: Virtually any look for granite, marble, or custom concrete can be easily achieved. Instead of replacing the counter top - with Granicrete Installations you simply resurface it. Granicrete has excellent adhesion to laminate, FormicaÂ®, tile, and wood countertops and quickly replicates the highest-end stone looks, chiseled edges, and easily creates tall back splashes. Our simple coloring system guarantees you will achieve that one-of-a-kind look.

OK, can't convert a file to jpg. My post is about granicrete. Got a brochure on the company telling me to go to their school (Farminton hills MI.) and be a granicrete installer. They say, among other things that this product can be layed over laminate, formica and MDF.

Granicrete is very durable, and, unlike granite, remains impermeable to water, food bacteria, harsh chemicals and stains. Granite, on the other hand, stains with certain fruits, oils, and retains bacteria. Granicrete is also seamless and uses a USDA approved epoxy coating, unlike granite.

Granicrete Installations can achieve virtually any look for granite, marble, stone, or custom concrete countertops..â¦or get the custom look that Ty Pennington preferred on Extreme Home Makeover! Granicrete is also used for the following applications: Raised Backsplashes, Bathroom Counters, Shower Panels, Bar Tops. Garage Floors, Patios, Driveways.

Granicrete Countertops is one of the hottest trends in the home improvement industry. Granicrete is used to design and build your custom counter top to match your decor and personality. You can have complete control of your new look. If you choose, you can see several custom samples before your countertop is installed. Some of the many advantages of Granicrete are: 1  Easy to clean. 2  Custom and beautiful design let your imagination get the look you desire. 3  Non porous â Food safe â Simple to clean and resists staining (USDA certified)  No more unsightly seams â Every top we install is completely 100% seamless.

I had Granicrete put on my countertops about 5 years ago. The coloration is great, but the product is not what it appears. The overlay of this product around my sink is pulling away from the formica underneath it. The edges in some places is so rough you could actually scrape you skin on it.

We had Granicrete installed in our kitchen about 2 1/2 years ago . It is the worst thing we could have ever done!! $ 2400.00 and it is crumbling around the edges, I have had to use a magic marker to fill where the edges have fallen off.

4/2014 We had 950 feet of our patio covered in this product. Granicrete! We spent $5,350 to have it done. Within a year, it started cracking and chipping off in certain places. Since then, I have been calling the business to have them come and fix it. I don't hear back and they don't show up. Each year it gets worse.
